# Makes a given loop or function (that the 'break' keyword is inside) act as it has completely ended its execution ("breaks" free from the loop/function)

# for example:
forever
    wait 1s
    
    Print "attempting to leave forever loop"
    if {Chance 20%}
        break
    end
end

func Test
    if {Chance 20%}
        break
    end
    
    Print "this will not run because the 'break' keyword was used"
end

run Test